Nyeri county plans to build a multimillion-shilling world centre for Boy Scouts. Nyeri Tourism executive Stanley Miano on Tuesday said the centre will be built in Nyeri town next to the Scouts founder Baden Powell&rsquo;s grave. It will be used for training and promoting Boy Scouts around the world.The county has approached the British High Commission.&ldquo;The founder of the Boy Scouts is laid to rest here so we want to take advantage to make it a bigger institution where people from all over the world can visit and get special training about the Boy Scouts Movement,&rdquo; Miano said.He spoke when he hosted secretary general of the World Organization of the Scout Movement Ahmad Alhendawi. Alhendawi had come to pay his respects and reconnect with Powell&rsquo;s legacy.